  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>To a certain extent, yes. &nbsp;
    Your religion is part of what determines your starting faction with NPC's in
    Norrath.&nbsp; Your starting religion&nbsp; will have an impact on what quests you can do.
    </font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Why
    do monsters run away when I blind them?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>They can't see you, so they can't
    find you to attack.&nbsp; They will wander around aimlessly until blindness wears off or
    they enter melee range.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Do
    I always get the same amount of exp on a res?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Yes, you do, provided it's the same
    res spell.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>I
    am always broke, any ideas on how to get money?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Look for creatures that drop
    weapons, as they are the most consistent source of money.&nbsp; From rusty to bronze to
    fine steel, they are a good&nbsp; source of money for whatever level range you are in.</font></small><p><small><font
    face='Arial'>You can also offer heals and resses for money as well.</font></small></p>
    <p><small><font face='Arial'>Alternative, you can kill monsters that drop unique items and
    resell them.&nbsp; However, some people frown upon camping items for the sole &nbsp;
    purpose of resale.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Is
    it worth getting plate armour - or should I focus on the more common stat enchancing chain
    armours?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>It's never worth buying plate from
    the stores.&nbsp; For a fraction of the cost and a noticible but manageable difference in
    weight, you can get bronze plate which as the same AC.&nbsp; However, since you're not
    expected to tank, it is usually a better idea to go for armor that&nbsp; enhances your
    wisdom, since wisdom increases the mana that you have.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><strong><small>My
    group abuses me if I melee during a fight - is there more to just medding and healing in
    combat?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Yes there is.&nbsp; You have spells
    that interrupt spellcasters (the stun line) which is incredibly useful in zones like Cazic
    Thule, where the casters are primarily clerics.&nbsp; Atone is useful in helping to pull a
    monster off an overzealous nuker.&nbsp; There are many utility spells you can use. &nbsp;
    However, as far as melee goes, you must realize that after level 20 or so that meleeing
    becomes tremendously less beneficial than just medding and casting.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Is
    there a &quot;best race&quot; for clerics?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>There are two races that people
    usually consider as the best races for clerics.&nbsp; The first is dwarves, because of the
    combination of high strength and wisdom.&nbsp; The second is high elves, simply because
    they can start with higher wisdom than any other class.&nbsp; However, none of the races
    are considerably different in statistics except gnomes, which have very low starting
    wisdom.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Is
    it true that Wisdom caps at 200?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>No, although the mana gain you
    receive for each point after 200 is much less than for each point before 200.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Is
    symbol like a rune or shieldskin spell? Will it wear off once they lose their extra hp?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>No, it is a buff spell that extends
    your maximum HP for the duration of the spell.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Can
    I bind people anywhere?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>No, other people can only be bound
    in city zones.&nbsp; Currently, the city&nbsp; zones in the game are: Greater Faydark,
    Felwithe (both), Akanon, Kaladim (both), Freeport (all 3), Grobb, Rivervale, Highkeep,
    Qeynos (both), Surefall Glade, Oggok, Arena, and Erudin (both), Neriak (all 3), Halas.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Why
    doesn't invis v undead work all the time?&nbsp; Some undead still hit me.</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Some undead creatures can see
    invisble, allowing them to see you while you are invisible.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Is
    there anything special I should know about using divine aura spells?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Yes, lots.&nbsp; When you first
    memorize it, it will remain greyed out because it takes 15 minutes for the spell to cycle.
    &nbsp; This is not a bug .&nbsp; The spell gives you about 15 to 20 seconds of
    invulnerability, during which time you cannot cast nor attack in melee.&nbsp; </font></small><p><small><font
    face='Arial'>The primary use of the spell is so that you are able to run when you get in
    over your head.&nbsp; This spell has saved me countless occasions giving me that extra
    push I needed to get to the zone, or to guards.&nbsp; Other uses of the spell include
    pulling all the monsters on yourself on purpose, then aura-ing to tank while the other
    group members attack them.&nbsp; This does not work too well because most monsters will
    realize you are invulnerable and attack the other players if they are hit by them.&nbsp; </font></small></p>
    <p><small><font face='Arial'>However, this side effect creates another interesting use for
    Divine Aura.&nbsp; If a tank is trying to pull a creature off of you and is unsuccessful,
    casting aura will cause the creature to immediately turn and attack the tank instead.
    &nbsp; Then, simply click the divine aura icon away, and you are free to cast again.
    &nbsp; </font></small></p>
    <p><small><font face='Arial'>The bottom line is, experiment.&nbsp; Aura has many unique
    properties which all can be used to your advantage, especially in group combat.&nbsp; It's
    my personal belief that a cleric should ALWAYS have this spell memorized.&nbsp; For those
    of you who believe you need the extra spell slot for something else, I'd like to remind
    you that casting divine aura will give you more than enough time to go to your spellbook
    and replace a spell with that one spell that you need for the current situation, no matter
    who is attacking you. </font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Why
    does the food and water I summon disappear after I go linkdead or log out?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Because that was Verant's intent
    :).&nbsp; All items that a cleric can summon will disappear upon logging out.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>What
    is atone good for?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Atone wipes the damage history and
    hate list from a monster.&nbsp; This has multiple uses.&nbsp; One, is if you wander close
    enough to a monster that it attacks you, and you don't want to deal with it, just root it,
    back off, and atone it.&nbsp; The monster will then leave you along.&nbsp; Another use is
    to wipe the hate list when someone has upset a monster beyond the tanks ability to taunt.<br>
    <br>
    Some people use this spell to &quot;twink&quot; people.&nbsp; A high level cleric can do
    almost all of the damage to a creature, atone it, and a lower level character can kill it
    and receive all the experience for killing it.&nbsp; However, this is frowned upon by some
    people.<br>
    <br>
    A word of caution.&nbsp; Some people have tried to use Atone and Memory Blur type spells
    to steal kills from another person or party.&nbsp; This is now classified as an EXPLOIT of
    this spell, and if reported to a Guide or GM, it is possible to receive a warning for
    this.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Will
    casting nullify or cancel magic aggro a mob on me?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>No, nullify and cancel magic are
    not considered offensive actions on an NPC.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>What's
    the point of our summoned hammers?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>They provide you with a magical
    blunt weapon whenever needed, and something to use when you have just died.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>What
    does the message &quot;this spell cannot take hold&quot; mean?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>It means your spell cannot co-exist
    with or cover an existing effect.&nbsp; This can be caused by:</font></small><ul>
      <li><small><font face='Arial'>A higher version of the spell was cast by another player.
        &nbsp; Center vs Courage for example.&nbsp; Another example would be Resurrect and
        Frenzied Strength (or any other spell that adds to stats).</font></small></li>
      <li><small><font face='Arial'>The same spell was cast on the target already by a higher
        level player.</font></small></li>
    </ul>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>I
    find that sometimes I can't recast my heals in time to save people.&nbsp; &gt;I just use
    my best heal spell every time - what am I doing wrong?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Try using a lower level heal spell
    or a buff spell.&nbsp; They tend to have shorter casting times than your highest level
    heal, and will often buy you enough time to cast that big heal spell.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Can
    I meditate just by sitting down?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Starting at level 35, yes.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Do
    my buffs work on other peoples pets?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Yes, provided that their pet starts
    with more than 10 hit points.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>What
    is a manastone? Where can I get one?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>A manastone is an object which used
    to enable you to convert your hp to mana.&nbsp;&nbsp; This made it more efficient for a
    cleric to recover mana quickly when used in conjunction with a health-regen spell. &nbsp;
    These have now been removed as a loot item and at this time cannot be obtained from NPC's.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Is
    there any armor which is just for Clerics?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Yes.&nbsp; There are two types. </font></small><p><small><font
    face='Arial'>One is the the Holy Armour obtained from Solusek Ro in the form of Quests.
    &nbsp; These include:&nbsp; the Chestplate of the Constant, Shield of the Devout, Boots of
    Reliance, Gauntlets of the Ardent, Vambraces of the Fervent, and Greaves of the
    Penitent.&nbsp;&nbsp; This armour is golden in colour.</font></small></p>
    <p><small><font face='Arial'>The other type is known as Ethereal Mist Armour and is
    obtained from the Plane of Hate.&nbsp; This is no-drop armour and is purple in hue. &nbsp;
    Some of it's items represent the best for Cleric's in the game at this time.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>What
    do diseases do? Is it worth being able to cure them?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Most diseases are not directly
    lethal, although some like Scourge are short duration DoT diseases that can indeed kill
    you, and very quickly at that.&nbsp; Most on the other hand have indirect effects such as
    slower health regen, or slower mana regen.&nbsp; Your cure spells are definitely
    worthwhile.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Is
    there anything I should know about the effects of healing in a fight?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Yes.&nbsp; Be aware that when you
    heal a player this counts towards the NPC's youa re fighting for taunt value and if you
    heal too often they will decide they should take you out of the picture and proceed to
    beat on you heavily.&nbsp; Make sure your tanks hammer their taunt button to try and keep
    them off you.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font face='Arial' color='#FFFFFF'><small><strong>Are
    there any special areas which are more Cleric friendly than others?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>To an extent.&nbsp; Dungeons like
    Befallen, Mistmoore, Lower Guk and Unrest have a heavy undead population making for great
    use of the Cleric undead damage spells.&nbsp; Other than that though Cleric's are always
    welcome in any zone/party for their unrivalled healing abilities.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
